.TH CODETRAIL 1 "2026-06-29" "DevCore 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codetrail \- change receipts and blast radius analysis for AI-generated code
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B codetrail
.RI [ COMMAND ]
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init [\-\-path PATH]
Initialize CodeTrail in the current project.
.TP
.B history FILE [\-n LIMIT] [\-\-path PATH]
Show change history for a file.
.TP
.B explain FILE [\-\-path PATH]
Explain why a file exists, its decisions, and dependents.
.TP
.B blast FILE [\-\-path PATH]
Show blast radius for a file (direct and indirect dependents).
.TP
.B ai\-log [\-n LIMIT] [\-\-source SOURCE]
Show AI-generated change receipts. Filter by source (cursor, copilot, claude, etc.).
.TP
.B risk [\-\-path PATH]
Show risk summary for the project (AI ratio, high-risk files).
.TP
.B hotspots [\-\-path PATH] [\-n LIMIT]
Find files with highest blast radius (most depended upon).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-path " " PATH
Project root directory (default: current directory).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .devcore/devcore.db
SQLite database storing change receipts.
.SH SEE ALSO
shipforge(1), devpulse(1)
